# Component Usage Patterns

All components must follow these standardized patterns for consistency.

## 1. Badge Component

**Add size variants when using Badge:**

```tsx
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'

// ✅ CORRECT - Use variants, not custom classes
<Badge variant="success">Active</Badge>
<Badge variant="warning">Pending</Badge>
<Badge variant="destructive">Error</Badge>
<Badge variant="info">Info</Badge>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't override with custom sizes
<Badge className="text-[10px]">  // Wrong
<Badge className="text-lg px-4 py-1">  // Wrong
```

**For status indicators, use StatusBadge instead:**

```tsx
import { StatusBadge } from '@/components/ui/status-badge'

// ✅ CORRECT - StatusBadge for statuses
<StatusBadge status="success" size="md">Completed</StatusBadge>
<StatusBadge status="warning" size="sm" dot>Pending</StatusBadge>
<StatusBadge status="error" animated>Failed</StatusBadge>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use Badge for statuses
<Badge variant="success">Completed</Badge>  // Use StatusBadge
```

**Badge variants:**
- `default` - Primary brand color
- `secondary` - Muted gray
- `destructive` - Red for errors
- `warning` - Orange for warnings
- `success` - Green for success
- `info` - Blue for information
- `outline` - Outlined text
- `system` - Monospace system badge
- `brand` - Brand accent

## 2. Button Component

**Use semantic button variants:**

```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic variants
<Button variant="default">Primary Action</Button>
<Button variant="secondary">Secondary Action</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">Subtle Action</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="success">Approve</Button>
<Button variant="warning">Review</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom button styles
<Button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600">  // Wrong
```

**Button hierarchy per page:**
- **One** `default` (primary) button
- Multiple `secondary` or `ghost` buttons as needed
- One `destructive` button if delete/remove action exists

**Loading states:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Consistent loading pattern
<Button disabled={isLoading}>
  {isLoading ? (
    <>
      <Loader2 className="animate-spin" />
      Loading...
    </>
  ) : (
    'Submit'
  )}
</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom loading states
<Button className={isLoading ? 'opacity-50' : ''}>  // Wrong
```

**Icon buttons:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Icon-only button
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" aria-label="Close">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Missing accessible name
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>
```

## 3. Card Component

**Always use Card component, not custom divs:**

```tsx
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent, CardFooter } from '@/components/ui/card'

// ✅ CORRECT - Standard card structure
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <p>Card content goes here</p>
  </CardContent>
  <CardFooter>
    <Button>Action</Button>
  </CardFooter>
</Card>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom card divs
<div className="rounded-lg border bg-white p-6">  // Use Card
  <h3>Title</h3>
  <p>Content</p>
</div>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't override card padding
<Card className="p-8">  {/* CardHeader/Content handle padding */}
```

**Card without header/footer:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Content-only card
<Card>
  <CardContent className="pt-6">
    <p>Simple card content</p>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

**Card borders:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use semantic border
<Card className="border">  {/* Uses semantic border token */}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't customize border colors
<Card className="border-blue-200">  // Wrong
<Card className="border-foundry-200">  // Wrong
<Card className="border-slate-200">  // Wrong
```

## 4. Dialog Component

**Use size prop, not custom widths:**

```tsx
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogFooter } from '@/components/ui/dialog'

// ✅ CORRECT - Use size prop
<Dialog>
  <DialogContent size="md">
    <DialogHeader>
      <DialogTitle>Dialog Title</DialogTitle>
    </DialogHeader>
    <div>Content</div>
    <DialogFooter>
      <Button variant="secondary" onClick={onClose}>Cancel</Button>
      <Button onClick={onSubmit}>Submit</Button>
    </DialogFooter>
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use custom widths
<DialogContent className="sm:max-w-[600px]">  // Use size="md"
<DialogContent className="max-w-3xl">  // Use size="lg"
```

**Dialog sizes:**
- `sm` - 425px (confirmations, small forms)
- `md` - 600px (standard forms, most dialogs)
- `lg` - 800px (complex forms, galleries)
- `default` - 512px (if size not specified)

**Dialog footer pattern:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Cancel on left, primary on right
<DialogFooter>
  <Button variant="secondary" onClick={onCancel}>
    Cancel
  </Button>
  <Button onClick={onSubmit}>
    Submit
  </Button>
</DialogFooter>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't reverse button order
<DialogFooter>
  <Button onClick={onSubmit}>Submit</Button>
  <Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>
</DialogFooter>
```

## 5. Sheet Component (Side Panels)

**Use Sheet for side panels, Dialog for centered modals:**

```tsx
import { Sheet, SheetContent, SheetHeader, SheetTitle } from '@/components/ui/sheet'

// ✅ CORRECT - Sheet for detail views
<Sheet>
  <SheetContent side="right" className="w-[480px]">
    <SheetHeader>
      <SheetTitle>Detail View</SheetTitle>
    </SheetHeader>
    <div>Content</div>
  </SheetContent>
</Sheet>

// When to use Sheet vs Dialog:
// Sheet: Detail views, sidebars, history panels
// Dialog: Forms, confirmations, focused actions
```

## 6. EmptyState Component

**Use EmptyState for zero-data views:**

```tsx
import { EmptyState } from '@/components/ui/empty-state'

// ✅ CORRECT - Standard empty state
<EmptyState
  title="No tasks yet"
  description="Get started by creating your first task"
  action={
    <Button onClick={onCreate}>
      <Plus className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
      Create Task
    </Button>
  }
