## 8. Tabs Component

**Use Tabs for view switching:**

```tsx
import { Tabs, TabsList, TabsTrigger, TabsContent } from '@/components/ui/tabs'

// ✅ CORRECT - Standard tabs
<Tabs defaultValue="all">
  <TabsList>
    <TabsTrigger value="all">All</TabsTrigger>
    <TabsTrigger value="active">Active</TabsTrigger>
    <TabsTrigger value="completed">Completed</TabsTrigger>
  </TabsList>
  <TabsContent value="all">
    <TaskList />
  </TabsContent>
</Tabs>
```

## 9. Skeleton Component

**Use Skeleton for loading states:**

```tsx
import { Skeleton } from '@/components/ui/skeleton'

// ✅ CORRECT - Loading skeleton
{isLoading ? (
  <div className="space-y-4">
    <Skeleton className="h-12 w-full" />
    <Skeleton className="h-12 w-full" />
    <Skeleton className="h-12 w-full" />
  </div>
) : (
  <TaskList tasks={tasks} />
)}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom loading states
<div className="animate-pulse bg-slate-200 h-12" />  // Use Skeleton
```

## 10. Alert Component

**Use Alert for informational messages:**

```tsx
import { Alert, AlertTitle, AlertDescription } from '@/components/ui/alert'

// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic alerts
<Alert variant="destructive">
  <AlertCircle className="h-4 w-4" />
  <AlertTitle>Error</AlertTitle>
  <AlertDescription>
    Something went wrong. Please try again.
  </AlertDescription>
</Alert>

<Alert variant="default">
  <Info className="h-4 w-4" />
  <AlertTitle>Note</AlertTitle>
  <AlertDescription>
    This action cannot be undone.
  </AlertDescription>
</Alert>
```

## Component Naming Convention

When creating custom components that wrap or extend base components:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Descriptive, purpose-based names
TaskStatusBadge.tsx  // Specific to task statuses
OrderCard.tsx        // Specific to orders
CreateTaskDialog.tsx // Specific action + component type

// ❌ WRONG - Generic or unclear names
MyBadge.tsx          // Too vague
CustomCard.tsx       // Doesn't describe purpose
Dialog2.tsx          // Version numbers indicate poor planning
```

## Quick Checklist

Before committing any component usage:

- [ ] Badges use semantic variants (not custom colors)
- [ ] StatusBadge used for all status indicators
- [ ] Buttons use semantic variants and include loading states
- [ ] Icon-only buttons have `aria-label`
- [ ] Cards use Card component (not custom divs)
- [ ] Card padding not overridden
- [ ] Dialogs use `size` prop (not custom widths)
- [ ] Dialog footers: Cancel left, Submit right
- [ ] EmptyState used for zero-data views
- [ ] Skeleton used for loading states
- [ ] Sheet used for side panels, Dialog for centered modals
